{
  "page": "Marwyn",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the captain of the guards, see <a href=\"/index.php/Marwyn_Belmore\" title=\"Marwyn Belmore\">Marwyn Belmore</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Archmaester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ae/Archmaester.svg/50px-Archmaester.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/ae/Archmaester.svg/75px-Archmaester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/ae/Archmaester.svg/100px-Archmaester.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Archmaester</span><br />Marwyn<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Mage</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Archmaester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ae/Archmaester.svg/50px-Archmaester.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/ae/Archmaester.svg/75px-Archmaester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/ae/Archmaester.svg/100px-Archmaester.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Marwyn the mage by nawia.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg/350px-Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"535\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg/525px-Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg/700px-Marwyn_the_mage_by_nawia.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Marwyn, by Nawia ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Marwyn the Mage</li><li>The Mage</li><li>The mastiff</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">Archmaester</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">higher mysteries</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafmarwyn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafmarwyn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (appears)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Marwyn</b>, also known as <b>Marwyn the Mage</b>, is an <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">archmaester</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Marwyn\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Marwyn</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Marwyn\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Marwyn</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Marwyn\" title=\"Category:Images of Marwyn\">Images of Marwyn</a></div>\n<p>Marwyn has a thick neck and a strong jaw. He is short and squat with enormous hands, a thick chest, and a hard <a href=\"/index.php/Ale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ale\">ale</a>-belly. The <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">archmaester</a> has white hair coming out of his nose and ears. Marwyn is <a href=\"http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/beetle-browed\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikt:beetle-browed\">beetle-browed</a>, his nose has been broken more than once, and his teeth are stained red from chewing <a href=\"/index.php/Sourleaf\" title=\"Sourleaf\">sourleaf</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Though he wears a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a>'s chain of many metals, Marwyn wears a leather jerkin instead of robes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> His ring, rod, and mask are made of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Other maesters consider Marwyn disreputable for keeping company with <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whores</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_wizard\" title=\"Hedge wizard\">hedge wizards</a>, sailors, and other <a href=\"/index.php/Lowborn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lowborn\">lowborn</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He can speak the languages of <a href=\"/index.php/Ibben\" title=\"Ibben\">Ibben</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Marwyn has unorthodox views of <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">magic</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and he often calls the rest of the archmaesters \"the grey <a href=\"/index.php/Sheep\" title=\"Sheep\">sheep</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marwyn's chambers are at the <a href=\"/index.php/Ravenry\" title=\"Ravenry\">Ravenry</a> on the <a href=\"/index.php/Isle_of_Ravens\" title=\"Isle of Ravens\">Isle of Ravens</a>. They are found at the top of a flight of stairs in the north tower of the castle, below the <a href=\"/index.php/Rookery\" title=\"Rookery\">rookery</a> of the black <a href=\"/index.php/Raven\" title=\"Raven\">ravens</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Marwyn has traveled the lands beyond the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>. He spent eight years in <a href=\"/index.php/Further_East\" title=\"Further East\">the east</a>, mapping distant lands, searching for lost books, and studying with <a href=\"/index.php/Warlocks\" title=\"Warlocks\">warlocks</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Shadowbinder\" title=\"Shadowbinder\">shadowbinders</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He encountered <a href=\"/index.php/Mirri_Maz_Duur\" title=\"Mirri Maz Duur\">Mirri Maz Duur</a> during his travels in <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai</a>, and taught her the <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">Common Tongue</a> and the secrets of the human body.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Marwyn's accounts of his travels confirmed reports that there are no living animals in Asshai.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafasshai-by-the-shadow.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafasshai-by-the-shadow.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marwyn was nicknamed \"Marwyn the Mage\" by Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Vaellyn\" title=\"Vaellyn\">Vaellyn</a> after his return to the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a>. The name was soon all over <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>, much to Vaellyn's displeasure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Before <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> was expelled from the Citadel for <a href=\"/index.php/Necromancy\" title=\"Necromancy\">necromancy</a> and vivisection, Marwyn was the only archmaester who liked his thoughts about dead souls leaving some residue in this world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Maryn is rumored to have killed a man with his fists.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marwyn is the author of a book, <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Book_of_Lost_Books\" title=\"The Book of Lost Books\">The Book of Lost Books</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marwyn.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b2/Marwyn.jpg/350px-Marwyn.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"228\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/b/b2/Marwyn.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marwyn.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Archmaester Marwyn, by Tiziano Baracchi © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Lhazar\" title=\"Lhazar\">Lhazar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Mirri_Maz_Duur\" title=\"Mirri Maz Duur\">Mirri Maz Duur</a> mentions to <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> that she was taught about human anatomy, as well as the <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">Common Tongue</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, by a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> named Marwyn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>On the way to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> explains to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> how he came to believe in the possibility of <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghosts</a>, and mentions that of all the <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaesters\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaesters\">archmaesters</a> only Marwyn gave the matter any thought.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Leo_Tyrell_(son_of_Moryn)\" title=\"Leo Tyrell (son of Moryn)\">Leo Tyrell</a> tells the group of novices and acolytes assembled at the <a href=\"/index.php/Quill_and_Tankard\" title=\"Quill and Tankard\">Quill and Tankard</a> that Marwyn believes the tales of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragons\">dragons</a> are true, and that he has managed to light a <a href=\"/index.php/Glass_candle\" title=\"Glass candle\">glass candle</a>. When <a href=\"/index.php/Armen\" title=\"Armen\">Armen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Roone\" title=\"Roone\">Roone</a> say that certain archmaesters consider Marwyn to be crazy, Leo shrugs and says it is a simple fact that \"the <a href=\"/index.php/Menagerie\" title=\"Menagerie\">menagerie</a> hates the <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">mastiff</a>\", meaning the archmaesters and Marwyn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In King's Landing, Qyburn explains to Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> why he was expelled from the Citadel, calling the archmaesters craven and saying that Marwyn calls them \"the grey sheep\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> a phrase Cersei comes to like.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the <a href=\"/index.php/Book_Tower\" title=\"Book Tower\">Book Tower</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Ten_Towers\" title=\"Ten Towers\">Ten Towers</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a> finds her uncle, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Harlaw\" title=\"Rodrik Harlaw\">Rodrik Harlaw</a>, reading Marwyn's <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Book_of_Lost_Books\" title=\"The Book of Lost Books\">The Book of Lost Books</a></i>. Rodrik says that Marwyn claims to have found three pages of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Signs_and_Portents\" title=\"Signs and Portents\">Signs and Portents</a></i>, a book of <a href=\"/index.php/Visions\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Visions\">visions</a> written down by <a href=\"/index.php/Daenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenys Targaryen\">Daenys the Dreamer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marwyn sees through his glass candle that <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> is coming to the Citadel, and sends <a href=\"/index.php/Alleras\" title=\"Alleras\">Alleras</a> to meet him at the <a href=\"/index.php/Seneschal%27s_Court\" title=\"Seneschal&#39;s Court\">Seneschal's Court</a>. Alleras talks with Sam, and brings him to Marwyn's chambers in the <a href=\"/index.php/Ravenry\" title=\"Ravenry\">Ravenry</a>. Marwyn listens to Samwell's story—that the late Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Aemon</a> believed <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> is the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_that_was_promised\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prince that was promised\">prince that was promised</a>—and states that he knows the <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">prophecy</a>, but does not trust it. After Alleras says that Aemon wanted to go to Daenerys to counsel and protect her, Marwyn says it may be a good thing that Aemon died before he arrived in Oldtown, or the archmaesters might have killed him as part of their efforts to rid the world of <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">magic</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Marwyn decides to travel to <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> in Aemon's place. He orders Samwell to keep quiet about Daenerys and the dragons, finish his studies, and then get back to the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> as fast as possible. He orders \"<a href=\"/index.php/Alchemist\" title=\"Alchemist\">Pate</a>\" to find Sam a sleeping cell in the Ravenry, where he will help Pate tend Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Walgrave\" title=\"Walgrave\">Walgrave</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Raven\" title=\"Raven\">ravens</a>, and he orders Alleras to look after Sam. Marwyn then leaves to catch the <a href=\"/index.php/Swan_ship\" title=\"Swan ship\">swan ship</a> <i><a href=\"/index.php/Cinnamon_Wind\" title=\"Cinnamon Wind\">Cinnamon Wind</a></i>, in order to travel swiftly to reach Daenerys before the Citadel's man does.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Marwyn\">Quotes by Marwyn</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Marwyn\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b7/Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png/350px-Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"505\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b7/Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png/525px-Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b7/Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png/700px-Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marwyn_the_Mage_by_Amuelia.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Marwyn and a <a href=\"/index.php/Glass_candle\" title=\"Glass candle\">glass candle</a>, by Amuelia ©</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Marwyn</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Gorghan\" title=\"Gorghan\">Gorghan</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Ghis\" title=\"Old Ghis\">Old Ghis</a> once wrote that a <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">prophecy</a> is like a treacherous woman. She takes your member in her mouth, and you moan with the pleasure of it and think, how sweet, how fine, how good this is... and then her teeth snap shut and your moans turn to screams. That is the nature of prophecy, said Gorghan. Prophecy will bite your prick off every time. Still ...<br /><b>Alleras</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Aemon</a> would have gone to <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">her</a> if he had the strength. He wanted <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">us</a> to send a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> to her, to counsel her and protect her and fetch her safely <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">home</a>.<br /><b>Marwyn</b>: Did he? Perhaps it's good that he died before he got to <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>. Elsewise the grey sheep might have had to kill him, and that would have made the poor old dears wring their wrinkled hands.<br /><b>Samwell</b>: Kill him? Why?<br /><b>Marwyn</b>: If I tell you, they may need to kill you too. Who do you think killed all the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragons\">dragons</a> the last time around? Gallant <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonslayer\" title=\"Dragonslayer\">dragonslayers</a> armed with swords? The world the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a> is building has no place in it for <a href=\"/index.php/Sorcery\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sorcery\">sorcery</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">prophecy</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Glass_candle\" title=\"Glass candle\">glass candles</a>, much less for dragons. Ask yourself why Aemon Targaryen was allowed to waste his life upon the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>, when by rights he should have been raised to <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">archmaester</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">His <i>blood</i></a> was why. He could not be trusted. No more than I can.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Marwyn, <a href=\"/index.php/Alleras\" title=\"Alleras\">Alleras</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Samwell</b>: B-b-but, the other <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaesters\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaesters\">archmaesters</a>... the <a href=\"/index.php/Seneschal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Seneschal\">Seneschal</a>... what should I tell them?<br />\n<b>Marwyn</b>: Tell them how wise and good they are. Tell them that <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Aemon</a> commanded you to put yourself into their hands. Tell them that you have always dreamed that one day you might be allowed to wear the <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters#Chain\" title=\"Maesters\">chain</a> and serve the greater good, that service is the highest honor, and obedience the highest virtue. But say nothing of <a href=\"/index.php/Prophecy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prophecy\">prophecies</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>, unless you fancy <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poison</a> in your porridge.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> and Marwyn</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Marwyn\">Quotes about Marwyn</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Marwyn\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Mirri</b>: Marwyn, he named himself. From <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">the sea</a>. Beyond the sea. The <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Lands</a>, he said. Sunset Lands. Where <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">men are iron</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">dragons rule</a>. He taught me <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">this speech</a>.<br /><b>Jorah</b>: A maester in Asshai. Tell me, Godswife, what did this Marwyn wear about his neck?<br /><b>Mirri</b>: A chain so tight it was like to choke him, Iron Lord, with links of many metals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Mirri_Maz_Duur\" title=\"Mirri Maz Duur\">Mirri Maz Duur</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Armen</b>: Marwyn is unsound. Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Perestan\" title=\"Perestan\">Perestan</a> would be the first to tell you that.<br /><b>Roone</b>: Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Ryam\" title=\"Ryam\">Ryam</a> says so too.<br /><b>Leo</b>: The sea is wet, the <a href=\"/index.php/Sun\" title=\"Sun\">sun</a> is warm, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Menagerie\" title=\"Menagerie\">menagerie</a> hates the <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">mastiff</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Armen\" title=\"Armen\">Armen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Roone\" title=\"Roone\">Roone</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Leo_Tyrell_(son_of_Moryn)\" title=\"Leo Tyrell (son of Moryn)\">Leo Tyrell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The Mage was not like other <a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\">maesters</a>. People said that he kept company with <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whores</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_wizard\" title=\"Hedge wizard\">hedge wizards</a>, talked with hairy <a href=\"/index.php/Ibbenese\" title=\"Ibbenese\">Ibbenese</a> and pitch-black <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Islanders\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Summer Islanders\">Summer Islanders</a> in their own tongues, and sacrificed to queer gods at the little sailors' temples down by the wharves. Men spoke of seeing him down in the undercity, in <a href=\"/index.php/Rat_pit\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rat pit\">rat pits</a> and black <a href=\"/index.php/Brothel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brothel\">brothels</a>, consorting with <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummers</a>, singers, <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a>, even beggars. Some even whispered that once he had killed a man with his fists.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcprologue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Pate_(novice)\" title=\"Pate (novice)\">Pate</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Marwyn wore a chain of many metals around his bull's neck. Save for that, he looked more like a dockside thug than a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Marwyn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiaf